  <hidden>true</hidden>
  <content>= Description =

This macro is a bridge for the Confluence Page Tree macro. It displays the list of pages in the specified page using the [[Document Tree Macro&gt;&gt;https://extensions.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Extension/Document%20Tree%20Macro]].

= Parameters =

|=Parameter|=Description|=Accepted values|=Default value|=Mandatory
|**root**|The space to show.|**@home** (list the pages under the home page of the space), **@self **(under this page), **@none** (all the pages of the space), **@parent** (all the pages in the parent space), or the name of a space|**@home**|No

= Example of usage =

{{code}}
{{confluence_pagetree root="Main" /}}
{{/code}}

= Result =

{{confluence_pagetree root="Main"/}}</content>
